Explanation:

We use dynamic programming to solve this problem. We create a 2D array (dp) of size (m+1)xn, where m is the length of pattern string p and n is the length of string s. We iterate through the pattern string p and string s, updating the dp array accordingly.

For each character in p, if it is a '*', we update the dp[i] value by taking the maximum of dp[i] and dp[i-1] + 1. This is because a '*' character matches any sequence of characters, so we need to consider the longest match from the previous character in s.

For each character in s, we update the dp[i] value by taking the maximum of dp[i] and dp[i-1]. This is because a non-'*' character in s matches the previous character in p.

Finally, we return the value at dp[m], which represents the length of the shortest substring in s that matches the pattern p.

